Date: Thu, 04 Nov 1999 10:52:11 +1100
From: Richard Russell <richardr@icpmr.wsahs.nsw.gov.au>

Further to the "emergence of DHF": In Australia it is considered that the
first description of cases of dengue haemorrhagic fever came from
Queensland in 1897.
Hare, F.E. The 1897 epidemic of dengue in North Queensland. Australasian
Medical Gazette 1898; 17: 98-107.
For a brief review of dengue in Australia see: Mackenzie, J.S. et al.
Dengue in Australia. J. Medical Microbiology 1996; 45: 159-161.
--
